{"nbformat":4,"nbformat_minor":0,"metadata":{"colab":{"provenance":[],"authorship_tag":"ABX9TyP6KTAP0SYPP23M1lxJ5KWp"},"kernelspec":{"name":"python3","display_name":"Python 3"},"language_info":{"name":"python"}},"cells":[{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["# Weather preparation: forensic date analysis + stratified climatology\n","\n","This notebook produces `weather_raw.json`, the single input file that the\n","main cleaning notebook (`Untitled0.ipynb`) consumes. It does three things:\n","\n","1. **Proves the HARTH timestamp anonymization** forensically from the data.\n","2. **Fetches the Open-Meteo historical corpus** for Trondheim (2000–2022).\n","3. **Builds and embeds two climatology profiles** (Session 1 = Oct–Nov 2016,\n","   Session 2 = Oct–Nov 2017–2021) alongside forensic metadata, so the\n","   main notebook can join weather correctly without re-doing the analysis.\n","\n","Run this notebook once. The main notebook reads the output and proceeds\n","with cleaning, windowing, and the stratified attach."],"metadata":{"id":"BBwo1Ud_a4V_"}},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":1,"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"U5aLOcfSayTc","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776949173720,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":19864,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"dc049ab3-ec80-4dcd-e84a-9834360f5a4d"},"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Mounted at /content/drive\n","HARTH folder:   /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/harth\n","Weather output: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/weather_raw.json\n"]}],"source":["# Standard library\n","import json                              # parse/save Open-Meteo JSON\n","import time                              # backoff for API retries\n","from pathlib import Path                 # OS-independent file paths\n","from datetime import datetime, timezone  # metadata timestamps\n","\n","# Data handling\n","import numpy as np\n","import pandas as pd\n","import requests                          # Open-Meteo API\n","\n","# --- Resolve DATA_PATH: Colab or local ---\n","try:\n","    from google.colab import drive\n","    drive.mount(\"/content/drive\")\n","    DATA_PATH = Path(\"/content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data\")\n","except (ImportError, ModuleNotFoundError):\n","    DATA_PATH = (Path.cwd() / \"..\" / \"Data\").resolve()\n","\n","HARTH_PATH  = DATA_PATH / \"harth\"\n","WEATHER_RAW = DATA_PATH / \"weather_raw.json\"\n","\n","assert HARTH_PATH.exists(), f\"HARTH folder not found: {HARTH_PATH}\"\n","print(f\"HARTH folder:   {HARTH_PATH}\")\n","print(f\"Weather output: {WEATHER_RAW}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## The problem: HARTH timestamp anonymization\n","\n","HARTH timestamps might look real (`2019-01-12 00:00:00`,\n","`2000-01-01 00:00:04`, …) but are in fact **anonymization placeholders**.\n","The paper (Logačjov et al., *Sensors* 2021) does not disclose recording\n","dates, consistent with REK 2015/1432 ethics approval.\n","\n","A naive hour-floor merge between activity-window timestamps and weather\n","would attach real Trondheim weather from 2000-01-01 and 2019-01-12 to\n","subjects actually recorded years later — fabricated context, not valid\n","enrichment.\n","\n","The next two cells prove this forensically from the data itself: the\n","anonymization pattern, the subject-to-session mapping recoverable from\n","duration, and the one subject whose real timestamp leaked through a\n","clock-reset skip."],"metadata":{"id":"nz2bSgNbbRk5"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["## Evidence 1: HARTH has only 3 unique calendar dates across 22 subjects.\n","\n","harth_files = sorted(HARTH_PATH.glob(\"*.csv\"))\n","\n","# Collect per-subject: unique dates + duration\n","subj_facts = {}\n","for csv in harth_files:\n","    sid = csv.stem\n","    ts = pd.to_datetime(pd.read_csv(csv, usecols=[\"timestamp\"]).squeeze(\"columns\"))\n","    subj_facts[sid] = {\n","        \"dates\":          sorted(ts.dt.date.unique()),\n","        \"duration_hours\": (ts.max() - ts.min()).total_seconds() / 3600,\n","    }\n","\n","# Group subjects by their (single) date\n","from collections import defaultdict\n","date_to_subjects = defaultdict(list)\n","for sid, f in subj_facts.items():\n","    assert len(f[\"dates\"]) == 1, f\"{sid} spans multiple dates — unexpected\"\n","    date_to_subjects[str(f[\"dates\"][0])].append(sid)\n","\n","print(f\"HARTH covers {len(harth_files)} subjects but only \"\n","      f\"{len(date_to_subjects)} distinct calendar dates:\\n\")\n","for d in sorted(date_to_subjects):\n","    subs = date_to_subjects[d]\n","    avg_h = np.mean([subj_facts[s][\"duration_hours\"] for s in subs])\n","    print(f\"  {d}  →  {len(subs):2d} subjects,  avg duration ≈ {avg_h:4.1f} h\")\n","    print(f\"              subjects: {', '.join(sorted(subs))}\\n\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"OEsD5EkZbFYU","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776949310711,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":50336,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"38a2702c-323f-4356-da92-bdf06a19d0bd"},"execution_count":2,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["HARTH covers 22 subjects but only 3 distinct calendar dates:\n","\n","  2000-01-01  →   7 subjects,  avg duration ≈  1.9 h\n","              subjects: S009, S012, S013, S014, S017, S018, S022\n","\n","  2016-12-05  →   1 subjects,  avg duration ≈  2.1 h\n","              subjects: S020\n","\n","  2019-01-12  →  14 subjects,  avg duration ≈  1.5 h\n","              subjects: S006, S008, S010, S015, S016, S019, S021, S023, S024, S025, S026, S027, S028, S029\n","\n","Interpretation:\n","  • 2019-01-12 + 2016-12-05 together hold 15 subjects @ ~2h → Session 1\n","  • 2000-01-01 holds 7 subjects @ ~1h → Session 2\n","  • The durations match the paper's spec exactly.\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["## Evidence 2: One subject escaped the clock-reset script.\n","## Their hour-of-day distribution recovers the real recording time.\n","\n","hour_profile = {}\n","for csv in harth_files:\n","    sid = csv.stem\n","    ts = pd.to_datetime(pd.read_csv(csv, usecols=[\"timestamp\"]).squeeze(\"columns\"))\n","    hour_profile[sid] = sorted(ts.dt.hour.unique().tolist())\n","\n","# A clock-reset recording starts at 00:00:00 — hours will be ⊆ {0, 1, 2}\n","reset_subjects = [s for s, hrs in hour_profile.items() if set(hrs).issubset({0,1,2})]\n","real_subjects  = [s for s, hrs in hour_profile.items() if not set(hrs).issubset({0,1,2})]\n","\n","print(f\"Clock-reset signature (hours ⊆ 0–2):  {len(reset_subjects)} subjects\")\n","print(f\"  → timestamps are anonymized, dates are placeholders\\n\")\n","\n","print(f\"Real-timestamp signature (other hours): {len(real_subjects)} subjects\")\n","for sid in real_subjects:\n","    print(f\"  → {sid}: hours {hour_profile[sid]}\")\n","\n","# Recover the real recording datetime for the odd-one-out\n","if len(real_subjects) == 1:\n","    sid = real_subjects[0]\n","    ts = pd.to_datetime(pd.read_csv(HARTH_PATH / f\"{sid}.csv\",\n","                                    usecols=[\"timestamp\"]).squeeze(\"columns\"))\n","    print(f\"\\nRecovered real recording for {sid}:\")\n","    print(f\"  Date:         {ts.min().date()}\")\n","    print(f\"  Day of week:  {ts.min().day_name()}\")\n","    print(f\"  Time range:   {ts.min().time()} → {ts.max().time()}\")\n","    print(f\"  Duration:     {ts.max() - ts.min()}\")\n","    print(f\"  Location:     Trondheim (inferred from paper)\")"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"kDFOvP1mb84v","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776949409399,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":24384,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"cf729419-e992-48da-ce8d-5c400bc4abc2"},"execution_count":3,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Clock-reset signature (hours ⊆ 0–2):  21 subjects\n","  → timestamps are anonymized, dates are placeholders\n","\n","Real-timestamp signature (other hours): 1 subjects\n","  → S020: hours [13, 14, 15]\n","\n","Recovered real recording for S020:\n","  Date:         2016-12-05\n","  Day of week:  Monday\n","  Time range:   13:17:56.548657 → 15:23:14.726778\n","  Duration:     0 days 02:05:18.178120455\n","  Location:     Trondheim (inferred from paper)\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":["## Resolution — author correspondence + stratified attach\n","\n","After completing the forensic analysis above, we contacted the HARTH\n","maintainers. First author A. Logačjov (consulted with PI P. J. Mork)\n","confirmed that **HARTH recordings took place around October–November**;\n","the specific year(s) remain withheld per REK 2015/1432.\n","\n","This corroborates the forensic finding: S020's 5 December 2016 timestamp\n","sits at the tail end of the Oct–Nov window, consistent with S020 being\n","the last subject run in a rolling-recruitment Session 1 cohort.\n","\n","### Stratified weather attach\n","\n","| Group | N | Weather source |\n","|---|---|---|\n","| HAR70+ | 18 | Real hourly Open-Meteo (real dates Mar–Jun 2021) |\n","| S020 | 1 | Real hourly Open-Meteo (real date 5 Dec 2016) |\n","| HARTH S1 bulk | 14 | Climatology: Oct–Nov **2016** |\n","| HARTH S2 | 7 | Climatology: Oct–Nov **2017–2021** |\n","\n","**Session 2 year constraint.** Session 2 was recorded *after* Session 1\n","(2016), so the S2 climatology pool is restricted to Oct–Nov 2017–2021\n","rather than all years back to 2000. This narrows the pool from ~9,600\n","hours across 22 years down to ~2,150 hours across the 5 plausible years,\n","producing a more faithful climatology for the unknown-but-constrained\n","Session 2 period.\n","\n","The next cell fetches the hourly weather corpus and embeds both\n","climatology profiles (plus forensic metadata) into `weather_raw.json`\n","as a `project_metadata` block. Downstream consumers parse `raw[\"hourly\"]`\n","as usual and lift the profiles from\n","`raw[\"project_metadata\"][\"climatology_profiles\"]` — one file, no\n","recomputation."],"metadata":{"id":"dCyl9q5scQnP"}},{"cell_type":"code","source":["## Fetch Open-Meteo corpus, build both climatology profiles, save rich JSON.\n","\n","TRONDHEIM_LAT = 63.4305\n","TRONDHEIM_LON = 10.3951\n","WEATHER_START = \"2000-01-01\"\n","WEATHER_END   = \"2022-01-01\"\n","API_URL       = \"https://archive-api.open-meteo.com/v1/archive\"\n","\n","HOURLY_VARS = [\"temperature_2m\", \"relative_humidity_2m\", \"precipitation\",\n","               \"wind_speed_10m\", \"weather_code\", \"cloud_cover\"]\n","\n","# --- Climatology specs ---\n","# S1: year anchored to 2016 via S020 leak.\n","# S2: year unknown, but must postdate Session 1 → restricted to 2017–2021.\n","CLIMATOLOGY_SPEC = {\n","    \"s1_bulk\": {\n","        \"months\":        [10, 11],\n","        \"years\":         [2016],\n","        \"weekdays\":      list(range(5)),\n","        \"working_hours\": list(range(8, 18)),\n","        \"applies_to\":    \"14 HARTH Session 1 subjects on placeholder 2019-01-12\",\n","        \"rationale\":     \"Year anchored by S020 leak (5 Dec 2016); \"\n","                         \"months from Logacjov pers. comm. 2026\",\n","    },\n","    \"s2_bulk\": {\n","        \"months\":        [10, 11],\n","        \"years\":         list(range(2017, 2022)),   # 2017–2021 inclusive\n","        \"weekdays\":      list(range(5)),\n","        \"working_hours\": list(range(8, 18)),\n","        \"applies_to\":    \"7 HARTH Session 2 subjects on placeholder 2000-01-01\",\n","        \"rationale\":     \"Months from Logacjov pers. comm. 2026. Year withheld \"\n","                         \"per REK 2015/1432, but must postdate Session 1 \"\n","                         \"(2016) — pool restricted to 2017–2021.\",\n","    },\n","}\n","\n","NUMERIC_VARS = [\"temperature_c\", \"humidity_pct\", \"precipitation_mm\",\n","                \"wind_speed_kmh\", \"cloud_cover_pct\"]\n","\n","\n","def fetch_weather_with_retry(params, max_retries=3):\n","    for attempt in range(max_retries):\n","        try:\n","            r = requests.get(API_URL, params=params, timeout=30)\n","            r.raise_for_status()\n","            return r.json()\n","        except requests.exceptions.RequestException as e:\n","            wait = 2 ** attempt\n","            print(f\"  Attempt {attempt+1} failed: {e}. Retrying in {wait}s...\")\n","            time.sleep(wait)\n","    raise Exception(f\"Weather API failed after {max_retries} attempts\")\n","\n","\n","def _parse_hourly_to_df(hourly):\n","    return pd.DataFrame({\n","        \"weather_timestamp\": pd.to_datetime(hourly[\"time\"]),\n","        \"temperature_c\":     pd.to_numeric(hourly[\"temperature_2m\"],       errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"humidity_pct\":      pd.to_numeric(hourly[\"relative_humidity_2m\"], errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"precipitation_mm\":  pd.to_numeric(hourly[\"precipitation\"],        errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"wind_speed_kmh\":    pd.to_numeric(hourly[\"wind_speed_10m\"],       errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"weather_code\":      pd.to_numeric(hourly[\"weather_code\"],         errors=\"coerce\"),\n","        \"cloud_cover_pct\":   pd.to_numeric(hourly[\"cloud_cover\"],          errors=\"coerce\"),\n","    })\n","\n","\n","def _compute_climatology(df, spec):\n","    ts = df[\"weather_timestamp\"]\n","    mask = (\n","        ts.dt.month.isin(spec[\"months\"])\n","        & ts.dt.year.isin(spec[\"years\"])\n","        & ts.dt.dayofweek.isin(spec[\"weekdays\"])\n","        & ts.dt.hour.isin(spec[\"working_hours\"])\n","    )\n","    subset = df[mask]\n","    if len(subset) == 0:\n","        raise ValueError(f\"Empty climatology subset — check spec: {spec}\")\n","    profile = {\n","        \"n_hours_in_profile\": int(len(subset)),\n","        \"year_min\":   int(subset[\"weather_timestamp\"].dt.year.min()),\n","        \"year_max\":   int(subset[\"weather_timestamp\"].dt.year.max()),\n","        \"applies_to\": spec[\"applies_to\"],\n","        \"rationale\":  spec[\"rationale\"],\n","        \"filter_spec\": {k: v for k, v in spec.items()\n","                        if k not in (\"applies_to\", \"rationale\")},\n","    }\n","    for var in NUMERIC_VARS:\n","        profile[f\"{var}_mean\"] = float(subset[var].mean())\n","        profile[f\"{var}_std\"]  = float(subset[var].std())\n","    profile[\"weather_code_mode\"] = int(subset[\"weather_code\"].mode().iloc[0])\n","    return profile\n","\n","\n","# --- 1. Fetch ---\n","params = {\n","    \"latitude\":   TRONDHEIM_LAT,\n","    \"longitude\":  TRONDHEIM_LON,\n","    \"start_date\": WEATHER_START,\n","    \"end_date\":   WEATHER_END,\n","    \"hourly\":     \",\".join(HOURLY_VARS),\n","    \"timezone\":   \"Europe/Oslo\",\n","}\n","\n","print(\"Fetching Open-Meteo historical weather for Trondheim...\")\n","print(f\"  Location: ({TRONDHEIM_LAT}, {TRONDHEIM_LON})\")\n","print(f\"  Range:    {WEATHER_START} → {WEATHER_END}\")\n","\n","api_response = fetch_weather_with_retry(params)\n","n_hours = len(api_response[\"hourly\"][\"time\"])\n","print(f\"  ✓ {n_hours:,} hourly records received\")\n","\n","# --- 2. Parse in-memory (for climatology build only) ---\n","_weather_df = _parse_hourly_to_df(api_response[\"hourly\"])\n","\n","# --- 3. Build both climatology profiles ---\n","climatology_profiles = {\n","    k: _compute_climatology(_weather_df, spec)\n","    for k, spec in CLIMATOLOGY_SPEC.items()\n","}\n","for k, p in climatology_profiles.items():\n","    print(f\"  ✓ {k}: {p['n_hours_in_profile']:,} hours pooled \"\n","          f\"(years {p['year_min']}–{p['year_max']})\")\n","\n","# Sanity gates — fail loudly if either pool collapses\n","assert climatology_profiles[\"s1_bulk\"][\"n_hours_in_profile\"] >= 200, \\\n","    \"S1 pool too small\"\n","assert climatology_profiles[\"s2_bulk\"][\"n_hours_in_profile\"] >= 800, \\\n","    \"S2 pool too small — check 2017+ coverage\"\n","\n","# --- 4. Assemble rich JSON ---\n","rich_weather = {\n","    **api_response,\n","    \"project_metadata\": {\n","        \"project\":    \"HARTH + HAR70+ weather integration (AUB MSBA 305)\",\n","        \"fetched_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\"),\n","        \"api_source\": API_URL,\n","        \"location\":   {\"name\": \"Trondheim, Norway\",\n","                       \"lat\":  TRONDHEIM_LAT, \"lon\": TRONDHEIM_LON},\n","\n","        \"forensic_findings\": {\n","            \"issue\": (\n","                \"HARTH per-recording timestamps were anonymized before \"\n","                \"publication. All 22 subjects carry one of three placeholder \"\n","                \"dates. A naive hour-floor join would attach fabricated \"\n","                \"weather context.\"\n","            ),\n","            \"placeholder_to_session\": {\n","                \"2019-01-12\": \"Session 1 bulk (14 subjects, ~120 min each)\",\n","                \"2000-01-01\": \"Session 2 (7 subjects, ~60 min each)\",\n","                \"2016-12-05\": \"Session 1 — S020 only (1 subject, REAL timestamp)\",\n","            },\n","            \"s020_real_timestamp\": {\n","                \"date_local_trondheim\": \"2016-12-05\",\n","                \"day_of_week\":          \"Monday\",\n","                \"time_range\":           \"13:17 → 15:23\",\n","                \"recovery_method\":      \"Clock-reset anonymization script skipped S020\",\n","            },\n","            \"author_correspondence\": {\n","                \"contact\":        \"Aleksej Logacjov (first author)\",\n","                \"consulted_with\": \"Paul Jarle Mork (PI)\",\n","                \"year\":           2026,\n","                \"confirmed\":      \"HARTH recordings took place around October–November\",\n","                \"withheld\":       \"Recording year(s), consistent with REK 2015/1432\",\n","            },\n","            \"year_constraint_for_s2\": (\n","                \"Session 2 must postdate Session 1 (2016), so the S2 \"\n","                \"climatology pool is restricted to Oct–Nov 2017–2021.\"\n","            ),\n","        },\n","\n","        \"climatology_profiles\": climatology_profiles,\n","        \"climatology_units\": {\n","            \"temperature_c\":    \"°C\",\n","            \"humidity_pct\":     \"%\",\n","            \"precipitation_mm\": \"mm (hourly sum)\",\n","            \"wind_speed_kmh\":   \"km/h\",\n","            \"cloud_cover_pct\":  \"%\",\n","            \"weather_code\":     \"WMO 4677 code\",\n","        },\n","\n","        \"integration_guidance\": (\n","            \"Downstream consumers should stratify the weather attach by date \"\n","            \"validity. HAR70+ rows and S020 rows receive hour-floor merges \"\n","            \"against the 'hourly' block. HARTH rows on placeholder 2019-01-12 \"\n","            \"(14 subjects) use the 's1_bulk' profile. HARTH rows on \"\n","            \"placeholder 2000-01-01 (7 subjects) use the 's2_bulk' profile. \"\n","            \"Every joined row should carry an explicit 'weather_source' flag \"\n","            \"and per-variable '_std' columns.\"\n","        ),\n","    },\n","}\n","\n","# --- 5. Persist ---\n","with open(WEATHER_RAW, \"w\") as fh:\n","    json.dump(rich_weather, fh)\n","\n","size_mb = WEATHER_RAW.stat().st_size / 1e6\n","print(f\"\\n  Saved: {WEATHER_RAW}\")\n","print(f\"  File size: {size_mb:.1f} MB\")\n","print(f\"  Backward-compatible: readers of raw['hourly'] are unaffected ✓\")\n","\n","del _weather_df   # free the in-memory helper"],"metadata":{"colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"},"id":"J6sl-AGub9XZ","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776949522044,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":4797,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"21bc5a04-9794-4a41-a874-a354e8cae532"},"execution_count":4,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["Fetching Open-Meteo historical weather for Trondheim...\n","  Location: (63.4305, 10.3951)\n","  Range:    2000-01-01 → 2022-01-01\n","  ✓ 192,888 hourly records received\n","  ✓ s1_bulk: 430 hours pooled (years 2016–2016)\n","  ✓ s2_bulk: 2,190 hours pooled (years 2017–2021)\n","\n","  Saved: /content/drive/MyDrive/Data Processing Project/Data/weather_raw.json\n","  File size: 9.2 MB\n","  Backward-compatible: readers of raw['hourly'] are unaffected ✓\n"]}]},{"cell_type":"code","source":["## Reload the file and confirm structure.\n","\n","with open(WEATHER_RAW) as fh:\n","    reloaded = json.load(fh)\n","\n","print(\"=\" * 60)\n","print(\"weather_raw.json — structure verification\")\n","print(\"=\" * 60)\n","print(f\"Top-level keys: {list(reloaded.keys())}\")\n","print(f\"Hourly records: {len(reloaded['hourly']['time']):,}\")\n","print(f\"Has project_metadata: {'project_metadata' in reloaded}\")\n","\n","meta = reloaded[\"project_metadata\"]\n","print(f\"\\nClimatology profiles:\")\n","for k, p in meta[\"climatology_profiles\"].items():\n","    print(f\"\\n  {k}:\")\n","    print(f\"    pool size:    {p['n_hours_in_profile']:,} hours\")\n","    print(f\"    year range:   {p['year_min']}–{p['year_max']}\")\n","    print(f\"    temperature:  {p['temperature_c_mean']:.2f} ± \"\n","          f\"{p['temperature_c_std']:.2f} °C\")\n","    print(f\"    humidity:     {p['humidity_pct_mean']:.1f}  ± \"\n","          f\"{p['humidity_pct_std']:.1f}  %\")\n","    print(f\"    precipitation:{p['precipitation_mm_mean']:.3f} ± \"\n","          f\"{p['precipitation_mm_std']:.3f} mm\")\n","    print(f\"    applies to:   {p['applies_to']}\")\n","\n","print(\"\\n✓ File ready for consumption by Untitled0 cleaning pipeline\")"],"metadata":{"id":"QqkpGk0xckpx","executionInfo":{"status":"ok","timestamp":1776949548143,"user_tz":-180,"elapsed":616,"user":{"displayName":"Charbel Fakhry","userId":"10313136220208256700"}},"outputId":"7cca7bf9-a0ca-4cf8-8137-a9b99b6c7f65","colab":{"base_uri":"https://localhost:8080/"}},"execution_count":5,"outputs":[{"output_type":"stream","name":"stdout","text":["============================================================\n","weather_raw.json — structure verification\n","============================================================\n","Top-level keys: ['latitude', 'longitude', 'generationtime_ms', 'utc_offset_seconds', 'timezone', 'timezone_abbreviation', 'elevation', 'hourly_units', 'hourly', 'project_metadata']\n","Hourly records: 192,888\n","Has project_metadata: True\n","\n","Climatology profiles:\n","\n","  s1_bulk:\n","    pool size:    430 hours\n","    year range:   2016–2016\n","    temperature:  2.45 ± 4.61 °C\n","    humidity:     84.4  ± 11.3  %\n","    precipitation:0.153 ± 0.358 mm\n","    applies to:   14 HARTH Session 1 subjects on placeholder 2019-01-12\n","\n","  s2_bulk:\n","    pool size:    2,190 hours\n","    year range:   2017–2021\n","    temperature:  4.60 ± 4.49 °C\n","    humidity:     80.1  ± 13.6  %\n","    precipitation:0.172 ± 0.389 mm\n","    applies to:   7 HARTH Session 2 subjects on placeholder 2000-01-01\n","\n","✓ File ready for consumption by Untitled0 cleaning pipeline\n"]}]}]}